# AkibaCore AI Guidelines

Apply these rules whenever writing, reviewing, or refactoring code in this repository.

## Work Style

- Read relevant files before editing.
- State assumptions when a request is ambiguous.
- Keep changes small and directly tied to the request.
- Avoid speculative abstractions, dependencies, and features.
- Match the existing style in edited files.
- Verify changes with commands, and report results.

## Project Context

- Backend: `shopanime_be`, NestJS, MySQL, API under `/api`.
- Frontend: `shopanime_fe`, React 19, Vite, Tailwind, React Router.
- Frontend shared API types: `shopanime_fe/src/lib/types.ts`.
- Frontend formatting helpers: `shopanime_fe/src/lib/format.ts`.
- Backend API/schema docs: `shopanime_be/API_DOCS.md`, `shopanime_be/database_schema.md`.

## TypeScript Rules

- Keep frontend strict.
- Do not introduce `any`, `as any`, `@ts-ignore`, or `@ts-expect-error`.
- Use `unknown` at unsafe boundaries, then narrow.
- Treat API numeric values as possibly `number | string`.
- Use existing shared types and helpers before creating new ones.

## Verification Commands

- Frontend typecheck: `npm --prefix shopanime_fe run typecheck`
- Frontend build: `npm --prefix shopanime_fe run build`
- Backend build: `npm run backend:build`
- Repo typecheck/lint: `npm run lint`
- Repo build: `npm run build`

## Safety Notes

- Do not run destructive schema rebuilds unless explicitly requested.
- Do not remove `shopanime_fe/index.html`; Vite needs it as the app entry.
- Do not edit `.env` secrets unless the user specifically asks.
